h2. Fix
# Remove the second fgmacedo from url: {{http://code.fgmacedo.com/talks/raw/5ff9e24367f647dad4e687674fcfacd806483331/pybr9_raspador/exemplos/sptrans_setembro.pdf}}
# Download will start.

When trying to import a repo, the import fails if the "owner" is set to a team entity.

For example, I have a team called "myorg", and when I import, I select "myorg" as the Owner in the "New Repository" section. I think run the import, and it fails, with the following entry:

{code}
13:21:00 fatal: No existing author found with &#x27;myorg&#x27;
{code}

However, I can import with my own user account as then owner, and then transfer ownership to &#x27;myorg&#x27; after the import has finished.

This occurred during a subversion (on-demand instance) to bitbucket git import.
